paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler
from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression
from pyspark.sql.functions import desc

uv = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///ds/uv_srs.parquet').select('date', 'time', 'duv', 'euv')
uv.createOrReplaceTempView('uv')

# uv = uv.filter('date like "201_-04-%"').filter('date > "2017-04-12"')
uv = uv.filter('date > "2017-04-12"')
# uv.sort(desc('date')).show()

assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=['euv'],
                            outputCol='features')

vector_uv = assembler.transform(uv.select('euv', 'duv'))

vector_uv = vector_uv.select('features', 'duv')
# vector_uv.show()

train_test = vector_uv.randomSplit([0.7, 0.3])
train = train_test[0]
test = train_test[1]

lr = LinearRegression(featuresCol='features',
                      labelCol='duv',
                      maxIter=10, regParam=0.0)

lr_model = lr.fit(train)
summary = lr_model.summary

print('Coefficients: %.4f' % lr_model.coefficients[0])
print('Intercept: %.4f' % lr_model.intercept)
print('RMSE = %.4f' % summary.rootMeanSquaredError)
print('r2 = %.4f' % summary.r2)
